Mountainsides and flood plains exist in the subtropics and temperate zones but in these regions there is progressively more of the in- between rolling country. The coastal plain around Townsville is largely flat even far away from any current river system - flat and seasonally swampy with small Melaleucas and the Coptotermes have to build mounds to keep out of the water in the wet season. In my yard amongst the rolling foothills of the Taylor Range in Brisbane, the Coptotermes don't need to build mounds but remain underground until they construct galleries to eat my fence or house. 



